      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An agent communication protocol (ACP) defines the vocabulary, message structure, and interaction patterns that autonomous agents use to talk to each other. Without a shared protocol two agents may exchange bytes but assign different meanings to the same field \u2014 the equivalent of two people speaking different languages at once. Protocols impose enough shared convention that agents authored independently can still interoperate, delegate tasks, negotiate, and report results correctly."
          }
        ]
      },
