      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Foundation for Intelligent Physical Agents (FIPA) standardised the first widely-adopted agent communication language in the late 1990s. FIPA-ACL introduced the concept of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "performatives"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 speech-act labels that convey intent alongside content. A modern LLM-based system may not implement FIPA-ACL literally, but the same conceptual layer (what is the sender trying to do?) appears in every practical protocol:"
          }
